params.to: Addresses to mint the tokens to.

params.admin: Address that receives DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE and can grant other roles.
params.backendSigner_: Address of the backend signer for transfer authorization.
params.initialBaseUriEpoch: Initial IPFS directory for token JSON, e.g. "ipfs://CID/".
params.reg: Optional epochs registry; pass address(0) if not used.

params.fromTokenId: The first token ID in the batch.
params.toTokenId: The last token ID in the batch.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.to: Address to mint the token to.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setBaseUriEpoch(string).details: Must be called by a trusted registry/manager after uploading new JSON snapshots to IPFS.

params.enabled: True to enable free transfers, false to require signature.

returns._0: True if the interface is supported.
The token URI at the epoch (format: ipfs://<CID_epoch>/<tokenId>.json).
An array of token IDs owned by the user.

batchMint(address[],uint256[]).notice: Batch mint tokens to multiple addresses with custom token IDs.

emitBatchMetadataUpdate(uint256,uint256).notice: Emit a batch metadata update event (EIP-4906).

setBackendSigner(address).notice: Set the backend signer address for transfer authorization.

setBaseUriEpoch(string).notice: Set the collection-wide base URI for the current epoch (ipfs://<CID_epoch>/).

setLoreRegistry(address).notice: Optionally set/replace the epochs registry pointer (read-only from NFT side).

setTransfersEnabled(bool).notice: Enable or disable free transfers without signature.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Get the token URI for a specific token.

tokenURIAtEpoch(uint256,uint64).notice: Get the token URI at a specific epoch.

tokensOfOwner(address).notice: Get all token IDs owned by a user.

transferWithSignature(address,address,ui.notice: Transfer a token with backend signature authorization.
